'Open MIC for Young Entrepreneurs, Erasmus+' 
                                                                      21st-28th of June, 2015 (County Wicklow/ Dublin City)

Increasing research shows that having formal education in current labour market doesn't guaranty employment. People requirer  to have a full set of social skills and creative approach to stand a chance of getting fulfilling employment position or/and to take on rewording road of self-employment by creating job opportunities for themselves. 

We believe that developing youth entrepreneurship skill is a way to start when addressing youth employment issues and examining current labour market. As well as that, the increase of social enterprises over the period of recession shows that people became more creative and more thoughtful about the needs of others during the difficult times. By organizing this seminar we not only want to work on the skill set, that we believe to be necessary to develop when flowing the path of entrepreneurship, but also celebrating all that good work that has been done by social enterprises and youth/community organizations who are working with young entrepreneurs! 

The main objective of  an 'Open MIC for Young Entrepreneurs, Erasmus+' seminar is to explore the concept of youth entrepreneurship and to exam ideas of social enterprises by using group knowledge as the main recourse,  Erasmus+ programme as a frame work and the following skill areas as a ground stones for entrepreneurs: Social and Emotional Intelligence, Collaboration, Articulation and Insight and Knowledge. By delivering this seminar we are aiming to: 
• To define the concepts of youth entrepreneurship and social enterprises;
• To explore possibilities that Erasmus+ offers for young entrepreneurs;
• To analyze the opportunities that Erasmus+ offers to social enterprises;
• To find out which parts in Erasmus+ supports organizations who are working/ intending to work with young entrepreneurs programs;
• To work on developing social and emotional intelligence, collaboration, articulation and critical thinking skills;
• To share good practice examples of being a young entrepreneur or working with young people who are developing their entrepreneurship skills;
• To explore strategies of successful social enterprises;
• To collect experiences, wisdom and strengths of participants and their organizations and document it in the form of magazine/ guidelines (later to publish it on-line and print 100 hard copies);
• To stimulate creative thinking and encourage future collaborations and networks between participating organizations. 

Our seminar is unique in a sense of group diversity. Participating organizations will send young people (18-30) who are counting themselves as entrepreneurs and workers/ volunteers who are developing programs and/or already working with youth entrepreneurship, as well as representatives of successful social enteritises.  We believe that having young people involved in this seminar makes it more real and beneficial to the group, as in the end of the day we are working WITH and FOR young people! We believe that there is enough events when we talk about young people without asking their opinion and exploring their views. That is way we want to carry out this project by supporting inclusion of young voices!

'Open MIC' will host participants from Ireland, Italy, Spain, Germany, Romania, Bulgaria, Ukraine, Poland, Netherlands and UK . It will take place in 2 different locations: first 5 days (4 nights) of the seminar will take place in County Wicklow, Kippure Estate and the second half of the seminar (3 nights) will take place in Dublin City Centre, Abbey Court Hostel on Bachelor's Walk, Dublin 1. In this way participants will get to see both- rural country and busy city lives of Ireland.

'Open MIC' seminar program consists of  5 different types of activities:
1. Daily activities: introduction to the program, evaluations and reflections;
2. The main workshops of the topics;
3. Experience shares 'Open MIC' sessions;
4. Guest workshops and successful social enterprise visit;
5. Collaborative action activities, such as group building, energizers and networking spaces. 

We believe that by taking part in an 'Open MIC' participants will  deepen their knowledge of youth entrepreneurship and social enterprises concepts and possibilities that Erasmus+ offers for young entrepreneurs and to social enterprises. They will receive practical tools when becoming and/or working with young entrepreneur and exam good practice examples of entrepreneurship and successful social enterprises. We also believe that an 'Open MIC' will be a possibility to further develop skills of self-awareness, confidence build, presentation and public speaking, oral/ written communication,  conflict resolution and decision making, critical thinking, networking and self expression through English.
